## Getting Started

```bash
# 1. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# 3. Copy env file and fill in values
cp .env.example .env

{% if has_docker %}
# 4. Start with Docker
docker compose up --build
{% else %}
# 4. Run locally
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
{% endif %}
```

